---
title: decode_receipt (osaka-blocks)
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    [*] --> q_init : start
    q_init --> q_check_type : isinstance(receipt, Bytes)
    q_check_type --> q_assert : receipt is Bytes
    q_check_type --> q_return_raw : receipt is not Bytes
    q_assert --> q_decode : assert receipt[0] in (1, 2, 3, 4)
    q_decode --> q_final : return rlp.decode_to(Receipt, receipt[1:])
    q_return_raw --> q_final : return receipt
    q_final --> [*] : done

    note right of q_assert
        INV: If receipt is Bytes, first byte must be
        in {1, 2, 3, 4} (assertion enforced)
    end note

    note right of q_decode
        INV: Decoded receipt strips the type prefix
        byte before RLP decoding
    end note

    note right of q_return_raw
        INV: Non-Bytes receipt is already a Receipt
        object and returned unchanged
    end note
